Authorities say during the operations 22 unlicensed firearms were recovered, 56 illegal liquor outlets closed down. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng police say they have arrested 2,871 over the last two days as part of their weekend crime prevention operations throughout the province. Authorities say during the operations 22 unlicensed firearms were recovered, 56 illegal liquor outlets closed down and one hundred and eighty suspects were arrested for the possession of marijuana. In the west rand, 221 suspects were arrested at road blocks and other operations. The police s Kay Makhubele says, The most challenging the business places where business robberies are taking place, more especially in Tshwane and Ekurhuleni where we arrested the most suspects and in Soweto. 